<section sectnbr = "1G">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "07">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A1706008" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Fuel Injector Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A1706007">Fuel Injector On-Vehicle Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
When performing the following procedure, be sure to observe 
<intxref refid = "AENCP70A1700001">Precautions for Fuel System Service</intxref>
 in order to reduce the risk of fire and personal injury.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A1706008001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Relieve fuel pressure. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1706003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove air cleaner assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1406004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect fuel injector connectors.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect fuel feed hose (4) from fuel delivery pipe (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fuel delivery pipe nuts (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove fuel injector(s) (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A171006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "65.567mm" ver = "01" gw = "199" gh = "169"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENCP70A1706008002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A1706009">Fuel Injector Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Reverse removal procedure noting following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Replace injector O-ring (1) and cushion (2) with new ones being careful not to damage them.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Apply thin coat of fuel to O-rings (1), and then install injectors (3) into delivery pipe (4) and cylinder head.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Make sure that injectors can be rotated smoothly (6). If not, probable cause is incorrect installation of O-ring. Replace O-ring with new one.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten fuel delivery pipe nuts (5) to specified torque and make sure that injectors can be rotated smoothly.
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T1G001">
<t-part>
Fuel delivery pipe nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
25
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
2.5
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
18.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A171007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "137.699mm" ver = "02" gw = "196" gh = "373"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After completing installation, check fuel line connections for leaks with engine not running and ignition “ON”. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1706004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
